main event: A civilian observed an unidentified bright object with erratic motion in Miamisburg, Ohio on August 15, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for over one hour.
The object was described as very bright or brighter than a star.
The sighting was classified as an AERO (STAR/PLANET) by Project Blue Book.
The report indicates there was no physical evidence associated with the sighting.
sighted object: a very bright or brighter than star object with erratic motion
